abstract: The British pound surged early Friday as exit polls indicated a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party, as talk of a China-U.S. trade deal buoyed share prices in Asia.
snippet: The British pound surged early Friday as exit polls indicated a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party, as talk of a China-U.S. trade deal buoyed share prices in Asia.
lead_paragraph: BANGKOK — The British pound surged early Friday as exit polls indicated a resounding election victory for Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party, as talk of a China-U.S. trade deal buoyed share prices in Asia.
headline_main: Pound Jumps on Expected Tory Win; Trade Talk Lifts Shares
headline_print_headline: Pound Jumps on Expected Tory Win; Trade Talk Lifts Shares

abstract: What drives Aung San Suu Kyi, the leader of Myanmar who this week defended her country at the International Court of Justice against charges that it carried out genocide against its Muslim Rohingya minority?

abstract: The city of Prague, the Czech capital, approved Thursday a partnership agreement with the capital of Taiwan, Taipei.
snippet: The city of Prague, the Czech capital, approved Thursday a partnership agreement with the capital of Taiwan, Taipei.
lead_paragraph: PRAGUE — The city of Prague, the Czech capital, approved Thursday a partnership agreement with the capital of Taiwan, Taipei.
headline_main: Prague to Ink Partnership With Taipei After Snubbing Beijing
headline_print_headline: Prague to Ink Partnership With Taipei After Snubbing Beijing

abstract: A frequent television commentator, Mr. Dershowitz often defended Mr. Trump publicly during the special counsel’s Russia investigation.
snippet: A frequent television commentator, Mr. Dershowitz often defended Mr. Trump publicly during the special counsel’s Russia investigation.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers are discussing hiring Alan Dershowitz, the famed lawyer whom the president has frequently reached out to for advice, to help with aspects of his impeachment defense in the all-but-certain Senate trial, people familiar with the discussions said.

abstract: Crowds have gathered for the past three evenings in a small park in downtown Myanmar's capital Yangon to hear accusations of genocide delivered thousands of miles away at the United Nation's top court in The Hague.
snippet: Crowds have gathered for the past three evenings in a small park in downtown Myanmar's capital Yangon to hear accusations of genocide delivered thousands of miles away at the United Nation's top court in The Hague.
lead_paragraph: YANGON — Crowds have gathered for the past three evenings in a small park in downtown Myanmar's capital Yangon to hear accusations of genocide delivered thousands of miles away at the United Nation's top court in The Hague.
headline_main: In Myanmar Park, Crowds Gather to Support Suu Kyi in Rohingya Genocide Hearings
headline_print_headline: In Myanmar Park, Crowds Gather to Support Suu Kyi in Rohingya Genocide Hearings

abstract: Ukraine's central bank sharply cut its key interest rate to 13.5% from 15.5% on Thursday, its lowest level in two years, thanks to slowing inflation, a strengthening hryvnia and the prospect of new loans from the International Monetary Fund.
snippet: Ukraine's central bank sharply cut its key interest rate to 13.5% from 15.5% on Thursday, its lowest level in two years, thanks to slowing inflation, a strengthening hryvnia and the prospect of new loans from the International Monetary Fund.
lead_paragraph: KIEV — Ukraine's central bank sharply cut its key interest rate to 13.5% from 15.5% on Thursday, its lowest level in two years, thanks to slowing inflation, a strengthening hryvnia and the prospect of new loans from the International Monetary Fund.
headline_main: Ukraine Central Bank Cuts Key Rate to Lowest in Two Years
headline_print_headline: Ukraine Central Bank Cuts Key Rate to Lowest in Two Years

abstract: The rapper’s show in Stockholm on Wednesday came just months after his trial for assault in the country drew international attention.
snippet: The rapper’s show in Stockholm on Wednesday came just months after his trial for assault in the country drew international attention.
lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM — When the rapper ASAP Rocky played an arena show in Stockholm on Wednesday night, it was the first time he had been to Sweden since August, when he was convicted over his part in a street brawl — a case that drew international attention when President Trump got involved.

abstract: A former Turkish prime minister established a new political party on Thursday, in a move that represents a challenge to President Recep Tayyip Erdogan's ruling party.
snippet: A former Turkish prime minister established a new political party on Thursday, in a move that represents a challenge to President Recep Tayyip Erdogan's ruling party.
lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey — A former Turkish prime minister established a new political party on Thursday, in a move that represents a challenge to President Recep Tayyip Erdogan's ruling party.
headline_main: Ex-Turkish Prime Minister Forms Party Challenging Erdogan
headline_print_headline: Ex-Turkish Prime Minister Forms Party Challenging Erdogan

abstract: Malaysian prime-minister-in-waiting Anwar Ibrahim said on Thursday he has given a statement to police after denying an accusation that he sexually assaulted a former aide a year ago.
snippet: Malaysian prime-minister-in-waiting Anwar Ibrahim said on Thursday he has given a statement to police after denying an accusation that he sexually assaulted a former aide a year ago.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Malaysian prime-minister-in-waiting Anwar Ibrahim said on Thursday he has given a statement to police after denying an accusation that he sexually assaulted a former aide a year ago.
headline_main: Malaysia's Anwar Gives Statement to Police After Denying Sexual Assault
headline_print_headline: Malaysia's Anwar Gives Statement to Police After Denying Sexual Assault
